Balsami-Roasted-Red-Onions Recipe

Ingredients
4 medium red onions, each cut into 8 wedges
4 tbsp. olive oil
6 sprigs fresh thyme, plus more for sprinkling
Kosher salt and pepper
2 tbsp. balsamic vinegar

Directions
1. Heat oven to 400Â°F. On a rimmed baking sheet, toss onions with oil, thyme and 3/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Roast 12 minutes.
2. Toss onions with vinegar and continue roasting until golden brown and tender, 10 to 15 minutes more. Transfer to a shallow bowl and sprinkle with thyme.

Content

About 85 calories, 7 g fat (1 g saturated), 1 g protein, 185 mg sodium, 6 g carb, 1 g fiber
